immerse /ɪˈmɜːs/

(immersing,immersed,immerses) 

1. V-T If you immerse yourself in something that you are doing, you become completely involved in it. 使专心于 

例： Their commitments do not permit them to immerse themselves in current affairs as fully as they might wish. 他们的职责不允许他们如其所愿地埋头于时事。 

2. immersed ADJ 专心的 [v-link ADJ 'in' n] 

例： He's really becoming immersed in his work. 他真正地变得专注于自己的工作。 

3. V-T If something is immersed in a liquid, someone puts it into the liquid so that it is completely covered. 使浸没 [usu passive] 

例： The electrodes are immersed in liquid. 电极被浸没在液体中。

